+# AI Memory OS v0.1 Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Extract existing memory infrastructure from `mcp-platform/memory/` into a standalone `ai-memory-os/` repository with a unified `memory` CLI.
+
+**Architecture:** Provider-based capture → processor → indexer → search, backed by SQLite FTS5 with optional Qdrant semantic search. CLI-first, with REST API and MCP server for agent integration.
+
+**Tech Stack:** Python 3.11+, FastAPI, SQLite (FTS5), Pydantic v2, optional Qdrant + Ollama embeddings.
+
+## Global Constraints
+
+- Python 3.11+ only; no system-level dependencies beyond what pip installs
+- SQLite FTS5 is the default search backend; Qdrant is optional and never required
+- All paths in vault-relative format (`wiki/generated/`, `raw/`, `wiki/hubs/`)
+- CLI commands are backwards-compatible within v0.x
+- Vault structure is stable: `raw/`, `wiki/generated/`, `wiki/hubs/` paths won't change
+- Every capture provider returns a `RawSource` pydantic model
+- Existing vault at `~/Obsidian/AI-Dev-Brain` is the test fixture for development
+
